A GET ALL order and a GET EVERY order. And a GIVE ALL and GIVE EVERY 
order.  ALL means all animate and inanimate objects other than the
actual unit or garrison of 10 soldiers (or 10 peasants).  Every means 
every inanimate object in possession.

For example, I'm in the same location as my noble g2r.  I want to leave 
all my ITEMs and some of my troops.  Instead of imputting 100 lines of 
GIVE orders, I can
GIVE g2r EVERY
GIVE g2r 12 10
GIVE g2r 286 5
get g2r 77 75	[ie:  I am taking back the specific amount of wood I 
		wanted to keep, but all my iron, elfstone, pikes, etc
		are now in his possession.

You might also write into the code that Ungarrison automatically has the
garrison GIVE [the ungarrisoning unit's id code] ALL.

Just a thought

Jim


