I suggest another column called "pos" for possessions...if the garrison 
has none, it shows a "-"    If it has anything, it shows a "yes".  Then a 
NEW ORDER, the castle owner may issue a "SHOW" order 

Example:  Garrison bo1g and bg7f have "yes" under the Pos column, all 
other garrisons do not.

w8l could issue:
SHOW bo1g (taking 1 day) and get a report:
garrison bo1g in aj91 reports it possesses 27 wood [77] and 33 stone [52]
	(whatever the numbers are for those items, you get the point)

note that although t0j has access to the garrisons because w8l is pledged 
to him, only w8l, the owner of the castle the garrison belongs to, can
request a report.  

Likewise, o1g has access to the bo1g garrison because it is the same 
faction as w8l, but he can only issue SHOW orders for his own garrison.


