> Allowing a castle to be independent of a city is something I wasn't
> considering; I was picturing cities being the center of economic
> and military development.  I suppose historically a city might have
> grown up around a military fortification, but I don't want players
> generating cities in the game.  Is it important that castles be
> able to be independent of cities?

No, I don't think it's very important.  I think that effectively in my
model everyone would end up wanting to build their castles in cities
anyway, precisely because that would give the most direct control over
the economic and military resources that the city provides.  Making it a
requirement wouldn't really make much difference at all, I think.

