Some more "ideas":

Short of making garrisons invulnerable, if it took longer to eliminate
garrisons (instead of 21 days to install one and 1 day to wipe it out)
that would make castles worth more.

Garrisons should report on everything that happens in their provinces.
Perhaps also have a chance of detecting stealth nobles (can "hounds" be
installed in garrisons?).

I suppose one could try to defend one's garrisons by putting more,
better trained men in them.  But I think that's a losing battle.  It's
always going to be too easy to concentrate force and take them out one
by one.

                                        David desJardins

