Greetings,

I liked the balances/changes. I do have a few concerns:

*Immunity from Vision -- While this is a great idea, I think there is a
potential problem. 1) I don't think the user of this spell should
_always_ receive the identity of the priesty using Vision. Maybe a
precentage would be better? If the % fails, the IfV user would still
notice the point total is decreased, indicating someone is attempting a
vision. If the IfV user always receives the identity, using vision
against other priests would never occur, for fear of retribution.

2) There should probably be a maximum of points from IfV. Priests, like
mages with aura, don't need to be walking about with an IfV value of 100
(though this might be _very_ difficult, given the casting time).

*I didn't recognize any problems with the free first tower, though maybe
as GM you did. It helps to establish the noble, and allows research
immediately.

*Will roaming mobs still attack buildings? It was unclear -- you wrote
the game wouldn't attack a wandering noble. I'm thinking of mobs
damaging an unoccupied inn by attacking. This is a Good Thing, IMO, and
should remain.



--jon
Eridanus
gabriel@ece.utexas.edu

