	The ACCEPT order is good but I think it could be a lot better
without too much work. The problem is that it still doesn't cover
ATTACKs and SURRENDERs which can dump tons of unwanted goods into your
inventory. Smart players will still find they need to do tons of drops
to get rid of things they never wanted.
	So...try any of these parameters for ACCEPT, and have the
implicit GIVEs done after ATTACKs and SURRENDERs go through the checks
as well. The special parameters should be cumulative with each other,
(ANDed together.) It's an issue whether you need to reset them every
turn or not.

	ACCEPT	<long integer>		# Accept as many of the offered
					  goods as possible without
					  exceeding <long integer>
					  weight. Rejects all GIVEs
					  if noble already carries
					  <long integer> weight or more.

	ACCEPT	stealth			# Accept any goods that don't
					  inhibit Conceal Self.

	ACCEPT	fly			# Accept any goods that don't
					  inhibit the flying movement
					  rate.

	ACCEPT	ride			# Accept any goods that don't
					  inhibit the riding movement
					  rate.

	ACCEPT  walk			# Accept any goods that don't
					  inhibit the walking movement
					  rate.

	Also, something that will prevent TONS of blown orders. How
many times I've needed this when I've wanted to change rulers in a
castle...

	GIVE <unit> all			# Dump entire inventory into
					  target unit's inventory.

	Tom	:-)

