	After reading the WWW page, these issues still appear
unaddressed.

	1.  No 'hostile all' command. This combines with...
	2.  No check against anonymity privileges of newly
	    formed nobles and newly built structures.
	3.  Sublocations are still ATTACKable as structures.

	Barring exceptionally long order queues, a newly formed noble
can get up to 29 days of travel, fighting, etc. with no attacks made
against him.
	The newly built structure gives one turn's grace against any
attacker, so long as the builder starts day 1 with Construction and
enough wood or stone.
	IDEA: Have new nobles and structures appear on day 30 of
the month in which they are created. If a building noble doesn't
move all turn, he's placed inside the structure.
	The AOO are currently using item 3 to detect whenever any
sublocation in their vicinity becomes occupied and then immediately
attacking via a pre-queued HOSTILE order. I don't know if it works,
but they're trying. :-)

