Here are my comments on the Olympia 2 changes, So you know where I'm coming
from I'm part of the 'Empire' that used to be headed  by Jeremy Maiden. I
consider out alliance one of the strongest and oldest but I still oppose some
of your changes as they favor the old guard over newbies.

Beastmastery
What I particularly like: change # 2

I did not like #3, It would give you only 1 or 2 monsters when you fight a
group and have capture beast in combat. It will give older more established
alliances an edge over the newer alliances. It should remain as is

Combat
What I particularly liked was changes 2,4,5,6,7

number 3 was that you'd only get half of a nobles stuff if you captured him.
This didn't make any sense. when you capture someone you should get all their
stuff. 

number 6: this is not enough. I never used the defence, swordplay, etc.
because they were too little gain for too much time. 2 points over one is
still not enough. How about a sliding scale? 4 or 5 points for each until
your at 100, 3 or 4 til 125, etc.

Castle
What I particularly like was change # 3
 
Change 2, making castles weaker in the beginning and able to be built up as
time goes on. I like the idea but the defence values don't go high enough.
Castles play little part in many of our wars because they are just too weak.
They should start at atleast value 50 and go up drastically from there.

Changes 8 and 10 I oppose because I like  the system as is. Money was always
short and if you want to get your money from taxing your fiefs then you
should be able to. You shouldn't have to be a trader and a taxing noble.

Tunnells- I love this Idea! it's the best change yet, I love the quest too.

Religion
I hate change number 6! Who's going to blow a noble point to resurect my
mage? Characters die all the time from stupid accidents, If my ten point mage
dies because I flew over water at the end of my turn then I would most likely
drop out. No ones going to resurect him and I'm not going to spend that much
time learning stuff again.
I hate change number 6.

Magic
I particularly like change number 7

4) trance should be left as is, there should be some way to get all of your
mana points back

8) I also like this as is

Sincerely,
Mike Moore
